<div class="container">
    <h1>HTML Minifier and Compressor Tool</h1>
    <p>Welcome to our HTML Minifier tool. Use this tool to minify your HTML code quickly and easily. Minifying your HTML helps to reduce file size and improve load times for your website.</p>

    <div class="minContainer">
        <textarea id="inputHTML" placeholder="Enter your HTML here..."></textarea>
        <textarea id="outputHTML" placeholder="Minified HTML will appear here..." readonly></textarea>
        <button onclick="minifyHTML()">Minify HTML</button>
    </div>

    <h2>API Documentation</h2>
    <p>Our HTML Minifier API allows you to minify HTML programmatically. Below is a brief guide on how to use the API.</p>
    <h3>Endpoint</h3>
    <pre><code class="keyword">POST</code> <code class="string">https://www.grovixlab.com/api/minify/html</code></pre>

    <h3>Request Body</h3>
    <p>The API expects a JSON object with the following structure:</p>
    <pre><code>{
    <span class="property">"html"</span><span class="operator">:</span> <span class="string">"your-html-code-here"</span>
}</code></pre>

    <h3>Response</h3>
    <p>The API will return a JSON object with the minified HTML:</p>
    <pre><code>{
    <span class="property">"minifiedHTML"</span><span class="operator">:</span> <span class="string">"minified-html-code-here"</span>
}</code></pre>
    <p>In case of an error, the response will contain an error message.</p>
</div>

<script>
    function minifyHTML() {
        const inputHTML = document.getElementById('inputHTML').value;

        fetch('https://www.grovixlab.com/api/minify/html', {
            method: 'POST',
            headers: {
                'Content-Type': 'application/json'
            },
            body: JSON.stringify({ html: inputHTML })
        })
            .then(response => response.json())
            .then(data => {
                if (data.error) {
                    alert('Error: ' + data.error);
                } else {
                    document.getElementById('outputHTML').value = data.minifiedHTML;
                }
            })
            .catch(error => {
                alert('Error: ' + error);
            });
    }
</script>
